{
  "video_id": "KaY8zqYfQI0",
  "title": "The Pantheon",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 4690.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4690.0,
      "end_time": 7230.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: We're\r\nstanding in the piazza,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7230.0,
      "end_time": 8882.0,
      "text": "the square in front\r\nof the Pantheon."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8882.0,
      "end_time": 10340.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nThis is the best"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10340.0,
      "end_time": 12300.0,
      "text": "preserved ancient\r\nRoman monument."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12300.0,
      "end_time": 14077.0,
      "text": "And yet, look at\r\nthe sense of age."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14077.0,
      "end_time": 15035.0,
      "text": "Look at the weathering."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 15035.0,
      "end_time": 17380.0,
      "text": "Look at the way in\r\nwhich its history is"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 17380.0,
      "end_time": 18950.0,
      "text": "revealed through its surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 18950.0,
      "end_time": 20040.0,
      "text": "It's been attacked."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 20040.0,
      "end_time": 23390.0,
      "text": "Its original bronze fittings\r\nhave been ripped off."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 23390.0,
      "end_time": 25680.0,
      "text": "Look at the numerous\r\nholes, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 25680.0,
      "end_time": 28840.0,
      "text": "in pediment, that tell of\r\nall the different purposes"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 28840.0,
      "end_time": 30480.0,
      "text": "that this building\r\nhas been put to."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 30480.0,
      "end_time": 32600.0,
      "text": "Originally a temple\r\nto the gods, then"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 32600.0,
      "end_time": 34630.0,
      "text": "sanctified and\r\nmade into a church."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 34630.0,
      "end_time": 36950.0,
      "text": "Now of course, it's also a\r\nmajor tourist attraction."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 36950.0,
      "end_time": 40460.0,
      "text": "This is a building that has\r\nhad just a tremendously complex"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 40460.0,
      "end_time": 40960.0,
      "text": "history."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 40960.0,
      "end_time": 43549.0,
      "text": "And you can see it\r\nall over its surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 43549.0,
      "end_time": 46090.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: We're seeing\r\nit very differently than anyone"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 46090.0,
      "end_time": 47610.0,
      "text": "in antiquity would have seen it."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 47610.0,
      "end_time": 48985.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nIn fact, we're"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 48985.0,
      "end_time": 51020.0,
      "text": "standing many feet\r\nhigher than we"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 51020.0,
      "end_time": 52970.0,
      "text": "would have been in\r\nthe ancient world."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 52970.0,
      "end_time": 58160.0,
      "text": "Rome accumulated elevation\r\nfrom the debris of history."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 58160.0,
      "end_time": 60770.0,
      "text": "Once, you would have stepped up\r\nto the porch of the Pantheon."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 60770.0,
      "end_time": 63240.0,
      "text": "Now, we actually lie downhill."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 63240.0,
      "end_time": 65850.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: And the\r\nspace in front of the Pantheon"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 65850.0,
      "end_time": 67787.0,
      "text": "was framed by a colonnade."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 67787.0,
      "end_time": 70120.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: The colonnade\r\nand the other buildings"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 70120.0,
      "end_time": 71661.0,
      "text": "that would have\r\noriginally surrounded"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 71661.0,
      "end_time": 73140.0,
      "text": "this building\r\nwould have obscured"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 73140.0,
      "end_time": 77370.0,
      "text": "the barrel on the side, and so\r\nthat we would have only seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 77370.0,
      "end_time": 78829.0,
      "text": "this very traditional\r\ntemple front."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 78829.0,
      "end_time": 79870.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Exactly."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 79870.0,
      "end_time": 82060.0,
      "text": "It would have been\r\nsomething very familiar."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 82060.0,
      "end_time": 84720.0,
      "text": "And the surprise\r\nwas what happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 84720.0,
      "end_time": 86620.0,
      "text": "as you approached the threshold."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 86620.0,
      "end_time": 88161.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nI have to tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 88161.0,
      "end_time": 90540.0,
      "text": "that I'm absolutely in love\r\nwith those massive columns."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 90540.0,
      "end_time": 93950.0,
      "text": "They are supported by these\r\nenormous marble bases."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 93950.0,
      "end_time": 98370.0,
      "text": "They rise up unarticulated,\r\nwithout any fluting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 98370.0,
      "end_time": 102480.0,
      "text": "and in these massive fragments\r\nof what were originally"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 102480.0,
      "end_time": 104640.0,
      "text": "marble Corinthian capitals."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 104640.0,
      "end_time": 105730.0,
      "text": "These are monoliths."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 105730.0,
      "end_time": 107520.0,
      "text": "They're single pieces of stone."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 107520.0,
      "end_time": 109780.0,
      "text": "Unlike Greek columns,\r\nthey were not segmented."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 109780.0,
      "end_time": 110650.0,
      "text": "They were not cut."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 110650.0,
      "end_time": 112250.0,
      "text": "And they were\r\nimported from Egypt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 112250.0,
      "end_time": 114400.0,
      "text": "which was symbolic\r\nof Rome's power"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 114400.0,
      "end_time": 117920.0,
      "text": "over most of the Mediterranean\r\nunder the emperor Hadrian, who"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 117920.0,
      "end_time": 120490.0,
      "text": "was responsible for the\r\nconstruction of this building."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 120490.0,
      "end_time": 121230.0,
      "text": "So let's go in."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 121230.0,
      "end_time": 122470.0,
      "text": "Let's go under the porch."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 122470.0,
      "end_time": 125460.0,
      "text": "Let's go through those\r\nmassive bronze doors."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 125460.0,
      "end_time": 129229.0,
      "text": "We just walked in under the\r\nstrictly rectilinear porch."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 129229.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131520.0,
      "text": "And then the space opens up."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 131520.0,
      "end_time": 134427.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Opens up\r\ninto this vast circular space."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 134427.0,
      "end_time": 136260.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: The\r\nwidth of the building"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 136260.0,
      "end_time": 137968.0,
      "text": "and the height of the\r\nbuilding completely"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 137968.0,
      "end_time": 139980.0,
      "text": "fills my field of vision."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 139980.0,
      "end_time": 142440.0,
      "text": "And it is, in a\r\nsense, an expression"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 142440.0,
      "end_time": 144870.0,
      "text": "of the limits of my sight."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 144870.0,
      "end_time": 148610.0,
      "text": "Unlike a basilica, this\r\nis a radial building."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 148610.0,
      "end_time": 151730.0,
      "text": "That is to say that it has\r\na central point and radiates"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 151730.0,
      "end_time": 153520.0,
      "text": "outward from that central point."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 153520.0,
      "end_time": 155780.0,
      "text": "But what's fascinating\r\nabout this building"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 155780.0,
      "end_time": 158400.0,
      "text": "is that it's not a\r\ntraditional radial structure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 158400.0,
      "end_time": 161170.0,
      "text": "in that the point\r\nwould be on the floor."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 161170.0,
      "end_time": 164210.0,
      "text": "The central point--\r\nits focus-- is midway"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 164210.0,
      "end_time": 166650.0,
      "text": "between the floor\r\nand the ceiling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 166650.0,
      "end_time": 168460.0,
      "text": "and midway between its walls."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 168460.0,
      "end_time": 172170.0,
      "text": "It is large enough, and\r\ngeometrically perfect enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 172170.0,
      "end_time": 174520.0,
      "text": "to accommodate a perfect sphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 174520.0,
      "end_time": 176520.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: And,\r\nas soon as you walk in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 176520.0,
      "end_time": 178810.0,
      "text": "you notice that there's\r\na kind of obsession"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 178810.0,
      "end_time": 182450.0,
      "text": "with circles, with\r\nrectangles, with squares,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 182450.0,
      "end_time": 185547.0,
      "text": "with those kinds of\r\nperfect geometrical shapes."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 185547.0,
      "end_time": 187130.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nThis is a structure"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 187130.0,
      "end_time": 190170.0,
      "text": "that is concerned with\r\nthe ideal geometries."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 190170.0,
      "end_time": 194092.0,
      "text": "But it also locates our place\r\nwithin those geometries."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 194092.0,
      "end_time": 195550.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS:\r\nBut the experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 195550.0,
      "end_time": 198190.0,
      "text": "of being in this space\r\nis anything but static."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 198190.0,
      "end_time": 200680.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: No, it's\r\nreally dynamic, in fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 200680.0,
      "end_time": 204240.0,
      "text": "One of the causes of that is if\r\nwe move our eye up the columns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 204240.0,
      "end_time": 205740.0,
      "text": "you can see that\r\nthey're beautifully"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 205740.0,
      "end_time": 209170.0,
      "text": "aligned with the\r\nfrieze of false windows"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 209170.0,
      "end_time": 210470.0,
      "text": "that are just above them."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 210470.0,
      "end_time": 212820.0,
      "text": "But then all of that does\r\nnot align with the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 212820.0,
      "end_time": 214070.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: That's right."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 214070.0,
      "end_time": 215600.0,
      "text": "They don't align\r\nwith the coffers"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 215600.0,
      "end_time": 217030.0,
      "text": "that we see in the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 217030.0,
      "end_time": 219000.0,
      "text": "What that does is\r\ncreates this feeling"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 219000.0,
      "end_time": 221510.0,
      "text": "that the barrel that\r\nthe dome rests on"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 221510.0,
      "end_time": 224470.0,
      "text": "is independent from\r\nthe dome, and almost"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 224470.0,
      "end_time": 226745.0,
      "text": "makes it feel as if\r\nthe dome could rotate."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 226745.0,
      "end_time": 228870.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: That\r\ncomplex visual relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 228870.0,
      "end_time": 232230.0,
      "text": "between the dome and the\r\ndecorative structures"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 232230.0,
      "end_time": 236660.0,
      "text": "in the barrel remind us that the\r\nactual structural system here"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 236660.0,
      "end_time": 239790.0,
      "text": "is dependent on concrete, and\r\nnot these decorative columns"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 239790.0,
      "end_time": 241120.0,
      "text": "that we see on the interior."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 241120.0,
      "end_time": 242161.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Exactly."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 242161.0,
      "end_time": 245380.0,
      "text": "There's thick, thick\r\nbarrel of concrete"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 245380.0,
      "end_time": 246900.0,
      "text": "that supports the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 246900.0,
      "end_time": 249940.0,
      "text": "Because a dome\r\npushes down and out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 249940.0,
      "end_time": 252530.0,
      "text": "Roman architects had\r\nto think about how"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 252530.0,
      "end_time": 255800.0,
      "text": "to support the weight\r\nand pressure of the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 255800.0,
      "end_time": 257570.0,
      "text": "And one of the things\r\nthat's doing that"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 257570.0,
      "end_time": 259945.0,
      "text": "are the thick concrete\r\nwalls of the barrel."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 259945.0,
      "end_time": 261570.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nYou know, the Romans"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 261570.0,
      "end_time": 263230.0,
      "text": "had really perfected concrete."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 263230.0,
      "end_time": 266330.0,
      "text": "And this is one of the buildings\r\nthat shows what was possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 266330.0,
      "end_time": 269410.0,
      "text": "This is shaping space, because\r\nconcrete could be continuous."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 269410.0,
      "end_time": 273050.0,
      "text": "It could be built upward\r\ncontinuously with wooden forms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 273050.0,
      "end_time": 276210.0,
      "text": "which would then be removed and\r\nthen could open the space up"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 276210.0,
      "end_time": 278544.0,
      "text": "in a way that post and lintel\r\narchitecture never could."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 278544.0,
      "end_time": 279960.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS:\r\nSo concrete could"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 279960.0,
      "end_time": 284190.0,
      "text": "be laid onto a wooden\r\nsupport or mold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 284190.0,
      "end_time": 287050.0,
      "text": "and could be shaped\r\nin a way that you"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 287050.0,
      "end_time": 289090.0,
      "text": "can't do with post and\r\nlintel architecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 289090.0,
      "end_time": 290631.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nWell, what it does"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 290631.0,
      "end_time": 293050.0,
      "text": "is it allows for this vast,\r\nopen, uninterrupted space."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 293050.0,
      "end_time": 295530.0,
      "text": "We walk into the space\r\nand we feel freed."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 295530.0,
      "end_time": 298330.0,
      "text": "We are given a tremendous\r\namount of freedom"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 298330.0,
      "end_time": 300747.0,
      "text": "in terms of how we move and\r\nhow we see through this space."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 300747.0,
      "end_time": 302996.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Because of\r\nthe Roman use of concrete,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 302996.0,
      "end_time": 304940.0,
      "text": "the idea that architecture\r\ncould be something"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 304940.0,
      "end_time": 309390.0,
      "text": "that shaped space and that\r\ncould have a different kind"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 309390.0,
      "end_time": 311100.0,
      "text": "of relationship to the viewer."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 311100.0,
      "end_time": 313890.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: It is even\r\nnow, in the 21st century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 313890.0,
      "end_time": 314660.0,
      "text": "awesome."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 314660.0,
      "end_time": 317160.0,
      "text": "The emperor Hadrian,\r\nunder whose direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 317160.0,
      "end_time": 320370.0,
      "text": "this building was constructed,\r\napparently loved the building"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 320370.0,
      "end_time": 323920.0,
      "text": "and loved to actually have\r\nvisitors come to him here."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 323920.0,
      "end_time": 326430.0,
      "text": "One could imagine him\r\neven in the back apse"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 326430.0,
      "end_time": 327614.0,
      "text": "opposite the entrance."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 327614.0,
      "end_time": 329280.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: The\r\nPantheon originally"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 329280.0,
      "end_time": 333940.0,
      "text": "contained sculptures of the\r\ngods, of the deified emperors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 333940.0,
      "end_time": 334690.0,
      "text": "we think."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 334690.0,
      "end_time": 336100.0,
      "text": "It really was about the divine."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 336100.0,
      "end_time": 340616.0,
      "text": "It was about the earthly sphere\r\nmeeting the heavenly sphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 340616.0,
      "end_time": 342240.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nAnd also in some way"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 342240.0,
      "end_time": 343840.0,
      "text": "about human perception."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 343840.0,
      "end_time": 345352.0,
      "text": "Look how rich the surface is."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 345352.0,
      "end_time": 346810.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS:\r\nAnd there would've"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 346810.0,
      "end_time": 350320.0,
      "text": "been much more in antiquity,\r\nwhen the coffers probably"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 350320.0,
      "end_time": 352490.0,
      "text": "had gilded rosettes."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 352490.0,
      "end_time": 356660.0,
      "text": "As we look at the drum,\r\nwe see colored marble."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 356660.0,
      "end_time": 359500.0,
      "text": "We see purples, and\r\noranges, and blues."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 359500.0,
      "end_time": 361250.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER:\r\nRemember, these marbles"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 361250.0,
      "end_time": 363920.0,
      "text": "are taken from around\r\nthe Roman Empire."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 363920.0,
      "end_time": 367210.0,
      "text": "So this is really an\r\nexpression of Hadrian's wealth"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 367210.0,
      "end_time": 368540.0,
      "text": "and Hadrian's power."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 368540.0,
      "end_time": 372180.0,
      "text": "This is the empire being able\r\nto reach across the globe"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 372180.0,
      "end_time": 374815.0,
      "text": "to draw in these\r\nprecious materials."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 374815.0,
      "end_time": 376920.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Perhaps\r\nthe most exciting part"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 376920.0,
      "end_time": 379140.0,
      "text": "of this space is the oculus."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 379140.0,
      "end_time": 383050.0,
      "text": "Because it almost\r\nseems to defy reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 383050.0,
      "end_time": 386450.0,
      "text": "How could there be a hole\r\nin the center of that dome?"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 386450.0,
      "end_time": 387659.0,
      "text": "It doesn't make sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 387659.0,
      "end_time": 389700.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: Well,\r\nit's the only light that"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 389700.0,
      "end_time": 392760.0,
      "text": "comes into this space, with the\r\nexception of some light wells"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 392760.0,
      "end_time": 395070.0,
      "text": "in some of the recessed\r\nareas, and of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 395070.0,
      "end_time": 397630.0,
      "text": "the grill just above the\r\ndoor, and the door itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 397630.0,
      "end_time": 399650.0,
      "text": "There is one great window."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 399650.0,
      "end_time": 402880.0,
      "text": "And my students for years\r\nhave asked, is there glass?"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 402880.0,
      "end_time": 404550.0,
      "text": "And of course, the answer is no."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 404550.0,
      "end_time": 406922.0,
      "text": "When it rains, the\r\nfloor gets wet."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 406922.0,
      "end_time": 409880.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: The perfect\r\ncircle of that oculus."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 409880.0,
      "end_time": 413420.0,
      "text": "The perfect circle of the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 413420.0,
      "end_time": 416310.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: The oculus\r\nis critical in the issues"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 416310.0,
      "end_time": 417922.0,
      "text": "that you had raised before."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 417922.0,
      "end_time": 419380.0,
      "text": "This is a building\r\nthat in some way"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 419380.0,
      "end_time": 422570.0,
      "text": "is a reflection of the\r\nmovement of the heavens."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 422570.0,
      "end_time": 427300.0,
      "text": "And what happens is light moves\r\ninto this space from the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 427300.0,
      "end_time": 430880.0,
      "text": "It projects often a very\r\nsharp circle on the dome,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 430880.0,
      "end_time": 434170.0,
      "text": "and moves across the\r\nfloor of the building"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 434170.0,
      "end_time": 436470.0,
      "text": "as the sun moves across\r\nthe sky, and then"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 436470.0,
      "end_time": 439350.0,
      "text": "eventually creeps up the\r\nother side of the dome."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 439350.0,
      "end_time": 442720.0,
      "text": "And so this entire building\r\nfunctions in some ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 442720.0,
      "end_time": 444430.0,
      "text": "almost like a sundial."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 444430.0,
      "end_time": 447470.0,
      "text": "It makes visible the\r\nmovements of the heavens"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 447470.0,
      "end_time": 450470.0,
      "text": "and makes them\r\nmanifest here on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 450470.0,
      "end_time": 452160.0,
      "text": "We've been talking\r\nabout this building"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 452160.0,
      "end_time": 454840.0,
      "text": "as a great monument\r\nof the ancient world."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 454840.0,
      "end_time": 456980.0,
      "text": "But it was admired and\r\ncopied in the Renaissance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 456980.0,
      "end_time": 460460.0,
      "text": "and in fact is perhaps the\r\nmost influential building"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 460460.0,
      "end_time": 462590.0,
      "text": "in architecture\r\nin the Renaissance"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 462590.0,
      "end_time": 463980.0,
      "text": "and in the modern era."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 463980.0,
      "end_time": 466540.0,
      "text": "I mean, think about all of\r\nthe different architects that"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 466540.0,
      "end_time": 467940.0,
      "text": "have referenced this building."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 467940.0,
      "end_time": 470140.0,
      "text": "I'm looking down at the\r\nfloors and the geometry"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 470140.0,
      "end_time": 472180.0,
      "text": "that you spoke of, the\r\ncircles and squares."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 472180.0,
      "end_time": 473638.0,
      "text": "And I'm thinking\r\nabout the pavement"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 473638.0,
      "end_time": 475200.0,
      "text": "in front of the\r\nGuggenheim Museum"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 475200.0,
      "end_time": 476760.0,
      "text": "on Fifth Avenue in New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 476760.0,
      "end_time": 479010.0,
      "text": "DR. BETH HARRIS: Actually,\r\nonce you know the Pantheon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 479010.0,
      "end_time": 482132.0,
      "text": "you begin to see copies of it\r\nand pieces of it everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 482132.0,
      "end_time": 483340.0,
      "text": "DR. STEVEN ZUCKER: It's true."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 483340.0,
      "end_time": 486300.0,
      "text": "The dome especially is perhaps\r\nthe most copied element,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 486300.0,
      "end_time": 487790.0,
      "text": "especially with the oculus."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 487790.0,
      "end_time": 490380.0,
      "text": "You can see that, for instance,\r\nin the National Gallery"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 490380.0,
      "end_time": 491160.0,
      "text": "in Washington."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 491160.0,
      "end_time": 494220.0,
      "text": "You can see it in almost\r\nevery Neoclassical building"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 494220.0,
      "end_time": 496380.0,
      "text": "in Europe and North America."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 496380.0,
      "end_time": 498895.0,
      "text": "But before we leave, I'd\r\nlove to go and pay homage"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 498895.0,
      "end_time": 501030.0,
      "text": "to Raphael, who's\r\nburied just over there."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 501030.0,
      "end_time": 511720.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    }
  ]
}